<p>
  Our audits help teams understand where their products fall short of WCAG 2.1 AA requirements and how to address those gaps. We assess web applications, documents, and digital tools used by Government of Canada staff and the public.
</p>

<h2>What we review</h2>
<ul class="list-disc mb-300">
  <li class="mb-75">Web applications and pages (desktop and mobile)</li>
  <li class="mb-75">Word, Excel, and PowerPoint documents</li>
  <li class="mb-75">PDF files</li>
  <li>Custom digital tools and internal applications</li>
</ul>

<h2>What you receive</h2>
<p>
  Deliverables include a written report with issue descriptions, relevant WCAG success criteria, severity ratings, and recommended fixes. We can also provide a follow-up review to verify that issues have been resolved.
</p>

<h2>How to request an audit</h2>
<p>
  Contact us at <a href="mailto:aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca">aaact-aatia@ssc-spc.gc.ca</a> to discuss your needs and schedule an audit. Include a brief description of the product and any known deadlines.
</p>

